# Portal page title (`PageTitleComponent`) and form back link (`PageBackLinkComponent`)

Canonical top-level heading for **portal shell pages** (dashboard, table, form, settings). Renders an `h1` plus optional muted subtitle above page content on the shell background — **not** inside table/form cards.

**Form create/edit pages** also require `PageBackLinkComponent` above the title — see **Form back link** below.

**Page titles and subtitles live on the page component** — **not** in `*.table.ts` or `*.form.ts`. Use `portal.<portal>.pages.*` keys only.

## `PageBackLinkComponent`

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| Path | `shared/ui/page-back-link/page-back-link.component.ts` |
| Selector | `app-page-back-link` |
| Inputs | `route` (required list URL from `app-urls.ts`); `labelKey` (required — reuse `portal.*.nav.all*` or `portal.user.nav.our*`); `form` (required `FormGroup` — dirty guard) |
| Import | Direct path — no barrel |

## `PageTitleComponent`

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| Path | `shared/ui/page-title/page-title.component.ts` |
| Selector | `app-page-title` |
| Inputs | `titleKey` (required i18n key); `subtitleKey` (optional i18n key — **required on every portal page**); `icon` (required `LucideIcon` — entity icon from portal page-icons); `entityTab` (optional `UserEntityTab` — tints decorative icon on user entity form/detail pages) |
| Import | Direct path — no barrel; add to page component `imports: [PageTitleComponent]` |

```typescript
import { PageTitleComponent } from '../../../../../shared/ui/page-title/page-title.component';
```

```html
<app-page-title [titleKey]="pageTitleKey" [subtitleKey]="pageSubtitleKey()" [icon]="pageIcon" entityTab="transport" />
```

User entity create/edit/detail pages: pass matching `entityTab` — see `entity-service-colors.mdc`. Hub / admin pages: omit (neutral icon).

Static keys:

```html
<app-page-title
  titleKey="portal.admin.pages.dashboard.title"
  subtitleKey="portal.admin.pages.dashboard.subtitle"
  [icon]="pageIcon"
/>
```

## Page icon (entity)

- **Required** on every portal page — Lucide entity icon left of the `h1` (decorative — no border or background).
- Source: `AdminPageIcons` (`portal/admin/admin-page-icons.ts`) or `UserPageIcons` (`portal/user/user-page-icons.ts`). Nav list items import the same constants — do not duplicate Lucide imports on pages.
- Use the **entity** icon (e.g. `LucideTruck` for vehicles), **not** `LucideSquarePlus`. Reserve `+` for sidebar create links and `PrimaryActionLinkComponent` only.
- Same icon on **list, create, and edit** pages for a feature — title copy differentiates the task.
- Icon size: **20px** in a **2.25rem** alignment box (`page-title.component.ts` → `iconInputs`).

```typescript
import { AdminPageIcons } from '../../../admin-page-icons';

protected readonly pageIcon = AdminPageIcons.vehicles;
```

## Visual styling (`page-title.component.scss`)

All page title chrome lives in `shared/ui/page-title/page-title.component.scss` — do not duplicate on feature pages.

**Icon**

- **Bare Lucide icon** — no border or background (decorative, not a control). Reserve bordered/filled icon chrome for clickable targets (buttons, tabs, icon buttons).
- `2.25rem` alignment box; icon color: `--metric-variant-default-icon`.

**Typography** (tokens from `theme-tokens.mdc` — do not hardcode sizes on feature pages)

- Title: `--font-size-page-title` / `--font-weight-bold`, `--line-height-tight`, `--letter-spacing-tight`; `--font-size-page-title-mobile` on mobile.
- Subtitle: `--font-size-body`, `--line-height-normal`, `--text-muted`, `max-width: 42rem`.

**Spacing**

- Title ↔ subtitle flex gap: `0.25rem` inside `.page-title__text`.
- Default block: `padding-bottom: 1rem`, `border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle)`, `margin-bottom: 1.25rem` — separates header from page body.
- Inside `.page-hub-header`: no border/padding on title block — hub wrapper owns the divider (after tabs).
- Inside `app-page-header` (title + create CTA): no border on title block — `PageHeaderComponent` draws the full-width divider when not in a hub.

## Layout (icon + title rows)

Flex row inside `PageTitleComponent`:

- **Column 1:** entity icon (`2.25rem` alignment box), **vertically centered** against the text block (`align-items: center` on `.page-title-block`).
- **Column 2:** `.page-title__text` — title + subtitle stacked (`gap: 0.25rem`). Subtitle `max-width: 42rem`.

Same flex pattern in `FormSectionComponent` (`.form-section-card__text`) — see `forms.mdc`.

## Header divider (page body separation)

| Context | Divider location |
|---------|------------------|
| Standalone `<app-page-title>` (Home, Offer, dashboard, forms, detail) | `.page-title-block` — `border-bottom` + `padding-bottom: 1rem` |
| `<app-page-header>` + create CTA (admin tables) | `.page-header` — full-width `border-bottom` |
| `.page-hub-header` (Find, Our listings) | Wrapper only — after tabs; no border on title or page-header inside |

Do not stack duplicate borders — `:host-context(.page-hub-header)` and `:host-context(.page-header)` remove border from `.page-title-block`.

## `PageHeaderComponent` (title + create CTA row)

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| Path | `shared/ui/page-header/page-header.component.ts` |
| Selector | `app-page-header` |
| Layout | Flex row: projected `app-page-title` (left) + `app-primary-action-link` or `[pageHeaderActions]` (right) |
| Alignment | `align-items: center` — CTA vertically centered against the full title block (icon + title + subtitle) |
| Divider | When **not** inside `.page-hub-header`: `padding-bottom: 1rem`, `border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle)`, `margin-bottom: 1.25rem` on `.page-header` — full-width divider under title + CTA. Title block inside has no border (via `:host-context(.page-header)`). |

Inside `.page-hub-header`, `PageHeaderComponent` drops border and bottom margin — tabs follow in the same header zone. See **User hub header** below.

## User hub header (Find / Our listings)

Find and Our listings group page title (+ optional `PageHeader` on Our listings) and `EntityTabsComponent` in a **`.page-hub-header`** wrapper — shared styles in `src/styles/_page-hub-header.scss`.

Hub page SCSS: `@use 'styles/page-hub-header';`

**Find** — title + tabs only:

```html
<div class="page-hub-header">
  <app-page-title … />
  <app-entity-tabs … />
</div>
```

**Our listings** — `PageHeader` (title + tab-specific create CTA) + tabs:

```html
<div class="page-hub-header">
  <app-page-header>
    <app-page-title … />
    <app-primary-action-link … />
  </app-page-header>
  <app-entity-tabs … />
</div>
```

Wrapper: `padding-bottom: 1rem`, `border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle)`, `margin-bottom: 1.25rem` before table content. `EntityTabsComponent` tightens top margin (`0.875rem`) inside the wrapper via `:host-context(.page-hub-header)`.

Reference: `portal/user/features/find/`, `portal/user/features/our-listings/`. See `entity-tabs.mdc`.

## Subtitle copy (UX)

- Explain what the user can do on the page — do not repeat the title.
- List pages: search, filter, or manage context.
- Stepper forms: mention the guided flow (e.g. *"Follow the steps below to create and schedule your shipment"*).
- Create vs edit: use different subtitles when it helps.
- **Detail pages (user portal):** static purpose copy only — **never** put route or warehouse data in the subtitle. Use `subtitleFind` / `subtitleOur` keys resolved by `resolveDetailSubtitleKey()`; entity identity (location + status) belongs in `EntityDetailSummaryComponent` — see `detail-page.mdc`.

## i18n key sources

All page header copy uses **`portal.<portal>.pages.<id>.title`** and **`.subtitle`**.

`portal.*.pages.*` entries in `en.json` / `bh.json` are **objects** `{ "title": "…", "subtitle": "…" }`, not flat strings.

| Page type | Page TS keys | i18n example |
|-----------|--------------|--------------|
| Table list | `pageTitleKey` / `pageSubtitleKey` constants | `portal.admin.pages.vehicles.title` |
| Form create | `pageTitleKey` / `pageSubtitleKey` constants or computed | `portal.admin.pages.createUser.title` |
| Form edit | computed from `isEdit()` | `portal.admin.pages.editUser.title` |
| Detail (user portal) | computed `pageSubtitleKey()` via `resolveDetailSubtitleKey()` | `portal.user.pages.viewTransport.subtitleFind` / `.subtitleOur` |
| Dashboard / settings | static in template | `portal.admin.pages.dashboard.title` |

## Where to render

**Page templates only** — first element above content (table card, form stepper, dashboard sections, etc.).

| Page type | Keys on page component | Example |
|-----------|------------------------|---------|
| Table list (with create route) | `pageTitleKey` + `pageSubtitleKey` + `PageHeaderComponent` + `PrimaryActionLinkComponent` | See **Title-row create CTA** below |
| Table list (read-only) | `pageTitleKey` + `pageSubtitleKey` + `pageIcon` | `<app-page-title [titleKey]="pageTitleKey" [subtitleKey]="pageSubtitleKey" [icon]="pageIcon" />` |
| Form create/edit (stepper CRUD) | `pageTitleKey()` + `pageSubtitleKey()` computed + `pageIcon` + `PageBackLinkComponent` | See **Form back link** below |
| Form create (single-step) | `pageTitleKey` + `pageSubtitleKey` + `pageIcon` + `PageBackLinkComponent` | See **Form back link** below |
| Detail (user portal) | `pageTitleKey` + computed `pageSubtitleKey()` + `pageIcon` + `PageBackLinkComponent` (no `[form]`) | See `detail-page.mdc` |
| Dashboard / settings | static `portal.<portal>.pages.*.title` + `.subtitle` + `pageIcon` | See static-keys example above |

Table pages with `tableMounted` remount: place the title row **outside** the `@if` so the title stays visible during refresh.

## Title-row create CTA (table list pages with create flow)

**Required** when the feature has a list route and a create route (admin CRUD, user list + create, etc.). Compose `PageHeaderComponent` + `PageTitleComponent` + `PrimaryActionLinkComponent` — **do not** put the CTA inside `PageTitleComponent` or `DataTableComponent`.

```html
<app-page-header>
  <app-page-title [titleKey]="pageTitleKey" [subtitleKey]="pageSubtitleKey" [icon]="pageIcon" />
  <app-primary-action-link [route]="createUrl" [labelKey]="createLabelKey" />
</app-page-header>

@if (tableMounted()) {
  <app-data-table … />
}
```

**Page component (parent owns route, title, subtitle, and CTA label):**

```typescript
import { PageHeaderComponent } from '…/shared/ui/page-header/page-header.component';
import { PageTitleComponent } from '…/shared/ui/page-title/page-title.component';
import { PrimaryActionLinkComponent } from '…/shared/ui/primary-action-link/primary-action-link.component';
import { AdminPageIcons } from '…/portal/admin/admin-page-icons';
import { ADMIN_CREATE_VEHICLE_URL } from '…/shared/constants/app-urls';

protected readonly pageTitleKey = 'portal.admin.pages.vehicles.title';
protected readonly pageSubtitleKey = 'portal.admin.pages.vehicles.subtitle';
protected readonly pageIcon = AdminPageIcons.vehicles;
protected readonly createUrl = ADMIN_CREATE_VEHICLE_URL;
protected readonly createLabelKey = 'portal.admin.nav.createVehicle';

imports: [PageHeaderComponent, PageTitleComponent, PrimaryActionLinkComponent, DataTableComponent, …],
```

- `createUrl` — create URL constant from `app-urls.ts` (never hardcode paths).
- `createLabelKey` — reuse matching `portal.<portal>.nav.create*` key when it exists.
- Place `app-page-header` **outside** `tableMounted` `@if` so title + CTA stay visible during table remount.
- Custom right-side actions: project into `app-page-header` with `pageHeaderActions` attribute instead of `app-primary-action-link`.
- **Read-only** table pages (no create route): standalone `<app-page-title>` only — no `PageHeader`.

## Form back link (create/edit pages)

**Required** on every portal create/edit form page. Renders above `PageTitleComponent` — returns to the entity list (admin: `portal.<portal>.nav.all*`; user: `portal.user.nav.our*`). Same URL as post-save redirect.

```html
<app-page-back-link [route]="backUrl" [labelKey]="backLabelKey" [form]="form" />
<app-page-title [titleKey]="pageTitleKey()" [subtitleKey]="pageSubtitleKey()" [icon]="pageIcon" />
```

```typescript
import { PageBackLinkComponent } from '…/shared/ui/page-back-link/page-back-link.component';
import { ADMIN_VEHICLES_URL } from '…/shared/constants/app-urls';

protected readonly backUrl = ADMIN_VEHICLES_URL;
protected readonly backLabelKey = 'portal.admin.nav.allVehicles';

imports: [PageBackLinkComponent, PageTitleComponent, FormPageComponent, …],
```

- `backUrl` — list URL from `app-urls.ts` (never hardcode paths).
- `backLabelKey` — reuse matching nav list label (`portal.admin.nav.allVehicles`, `portal.user.nav.myRoutes`, etc.).
- `[form]` — when dirty, `ConfirmService` prompts with `shared.form.common.discardChanges.*` before navigating.
- Component: `shared/ui/page-back-link/` — not inside `FormPageComponent`.

## Do not

- Put page `titleKey` / `subtitleKey` on `TableDefinition` or `FormDefinition` — pages own header copy.
- Do not add per-page back/cancel buttons in the form footer — use `PageBackLinkComponent` in the page template instead.
- Render page titles inside `DataTableComponent` or `FormPageComponent` — those frameworks handle table/form chrome only.
- Ship a portal page without a subtitle — always provide `subtitleKey` and matching i18n under `portal.*.pages.*`.
- Use inline `<h1 class="page-title">` or duplicate title SCSS on feature pages — styling lives in `page-title.component.scss` (+ `styles/_page-hub-header.scss` for hub wrappers only).
- Put Find / Our listings title and tabs as siblings without `.page-hub-header` — always wrap per **User hub header** above.
- Use `PageTitleComponent` on **guest** pages (login, register, landing) — guest pages keep their own auth/marketing title styles.
- Put create CTAs inside `PageTitleComponent` — use `PageHeaderComponent` + `PrimaryActionLinkComponent` on the page instead.
- Put border or background on page title icons — bare decorative icon only; use chrome on clickable controls.
- Put `LucideSquarePlus` on page titles — use entity icons from `AdminPageIcons` / `UserPageIcons`; `+` stays on create action links only.

